        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 400 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Villanow, or 8 miles
southwest of Dalton, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dalton, Chatsworth, Eton, Resaca, Ramhurst, Wood Station, Rocky Face,
Tilton, Mill Creek, Dawnville, Villanow, Nickelsville, and North
Georgia Speedway.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
